difficulty: The layout of the information and whether it ran together or was easy to see the different rows. Those made the difference of easy or difficult. Also whether I had to scroll across while remembering the title of the row. That was hard.
format: If the information was easy to find, if the table was easy to skim because there were lines between the rows or different colors of rows then I was satisfied. If it was hard to read, then I was not satisfied.
comments: Lines separating the rows (or colors) really helped.
